We recommended that Management:

Submit a written explanation why the foregoing violation was allowed to be committed for more than a decade;

Require the Municipal Assessor’s Office to properly classify, value and assess land properties on the basis of their actual uses regardless of where located, whoever owns them, and whoever uses them;

Submit the complete list of the real properties, together with their respective TDs, which remained not classified, valued and assessed based on their actual uses showing therein the comparison between the existing fair market values and assessed values and the correct fair market and assessed values according to actual uses in order for us to make a decision in audit; and,

Collect the back taxes of the land properties not properly classified, valued and assessed; if the same is not possible due to some legal restrictions, provide the said legal restrictions.

We recommended that Management:

Require strict compliance by the Bids and Awards Committee with the provisions of RA 9184 in the conduct of public bidding and awarding of the contracts/projects. BAC member, BAC secretariat and the TWG should familiarize themselves with different rules and regulations set forth by the said RA;

Adhere to the transparency provision as this is one of the governing principles on government procurement. BAC should invite in writing a representative NGO as observer as provided in the Section 13 of RA 9184 in all stages of the procurement process;

Strictly adhere to post all government procurement opportunities, results of bidding and related information such as supplemental bulletin in the PhilGEPS website;

Require the prospective bidders to post the required amount of performance security prior to contract signing to ensure faithful performance by the winning bidder of its obligation under the contract;


Ensure that bidders submit complete eligibility requirements and all documentary requirements prior to the signing of the contract; and,

Submit written justifications as to why violations to some provisions of RA 9184 were committed.

